#: ../../PyMOTW/textwrap/index.rst:156
msgid "Hanging Indents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../PyMOTW/textwrap/index.rst:158
msgid ""
"Besides the width of the output, you can control the indent of the first "
"line independently of subsequent lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../PyMOTW/textwrap/index.rst:165
msgid ""
"This makes it relatively easy to produce a hanging indent, where the first "
"line is indented less than the other lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../PyMOTW/textwrap/index.rst:184
msgid ""
"The indent values can include non-whitespace characters, too, so the hanging"
" indent can be prefixed with ``*`` to produce bullet points, etc. That came "
"in handy when I converted my old zwiki content so I could import it into "
"trac. I used the StructuredText package from Zope to parse the zwiki data, "
"then created a formatter to produce trac's wiki markup as output. Using "
":mod:`textwrap`, I was able to format the output pages so almost no manual "
"tweaking was needed after the conversion."
msgstr ""

